<TITLE> KU sets up inquiry committee following clashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, Apr 7 (bdnews24.com)  Khulna University authorities have formed a seven-member probe committee following clashes that took place between police and students that led to an indefinite closure of the university. The committee, headed by Professor Golam Mortuza, has been asked to submit its report within 15 days, SM Atiar Rahman, the university's deputy director of public relations, told bdnews24.com. The decision to establish the committee was taken at a syndicate meeting held Tuesday night, he said. The university police clashed with students following the confinement of a photo journalist of the daily Prothom Alo by some students. bd
